1. *Zvučalo* je kao da dolazi oluja. (It sounded like a storm was coming.)
2. Kada sam čuo kako *zvučiš*, pomislio sam da si ljut. (When I heard how you sounded, I thought you were angry.)
3. Da li ti *zvuči* dobro ideja da se vidimo večeras? (Does the idea of meeting tonight sound good to you?)
4. Oni su *zvučali* vrlo uvjerljivo, ali nisam im vjerovao. (They sounded very convincing, but I didn't believe them.)
5. *Zvučite* kao da znate o čemu govorite. (You sound like you know what you're talking about.)
6. Koliko dugo *zvoni* telefon pre nego što se javi sekretarica? (How long does the phone ring before the answering machine picks up?)
7. Kada *zvoni* telefon, uvek trčim da ga podignem. (Whenever the phone rings, I always run to answer it.)
8. Nikada ne zaboravljam da *ugasim* radio kada *zazvoni* telefon. (I never forget to turn off the radio when the phone rings.)
9. Njihov glas je *zvučao* tako toplo i prijateljski. (Their voice sounded so warm and friendly.)
10. Ako želite da se dobro *zvuči* na bini, morate vežbati svakodnevno. (If you want to sound good on stage, you have to practice every day.)